{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>Bfa1 is required for the spindle assembly checkpoint in budding yeast.  It functions in the same pathway with Bub2 in one of the branches of the spindle assembly checkpoint which prevents cytokinesis before the completion of chromosome segregation [[cite:PUB00083752], [cite:PUB00083753]]. Bub2 and Bfa1 are also required for the maintenance of G2/M arrest in response to DNA damage and to spindle misorientation [[cite:PUB00083754]]. The homologue of Bfa1 in fission yeast is Byr4, which together with Cdc16 (homologue of Bub2) forms a two-component GTPase-activating protein for Spg1 GTPase [[cite:PUB00083755], [cite:PUB00083756]]. Spg1 GTPase positively regulates septation and constriction of the actomyosin ring for cell division.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Bfa1 and Bub2 may function as a universal checkpoint in response to various checkpoint signals to avoid improper mitotic exit [[cite:PUB00083757]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure nil, :overlaps-with nil, :member-databases {"panther" {"PTHR35140" "MITOTIC CHECK POINT PROTEIN BFA1"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "GTPase activating protein complex, subunit Bfa1/Byr4", "short" "Bfa1/Byr4"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 0, "domain_architectures" 0, "proteomes" 1090, "taxa" 2945, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 1605, "sets" 0, "proteins" 1605, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 986}, "pathways" 0}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {}, :set-info nil, :accession "IPR034586", :literature {"PUB00083755" {"URL" nil, "issue" "17", "authors" ["Furge KA" "Wong K" "Armstrong J" "Balasubramanian M" "Albright CF."], "ISO_journal" "Curr. Biol.", "DOI_URL" "http://dx.doi.org/10.1016/S0960-9822(98)70394-X", "medline_journal" "Curr Biol", "title" "Byr4 and Cdc16 form a two-component GTPase-activating protein for the Spg1 GTPase that controls septation in fission y